-- Saipem Wins $894 Contract From Kuwait Oil Co. to Build Gas Booster Plant
-- Fiona MacDonald
-- 2010-06-17T13:19:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-17/saipem-wins-contract-valued-about-894-million-to-build-kuwait-gas-plant.html

          
          
             Kuwait Oil Co. signed a contract
with Saipem SpA of Italy valued at about 260 million dinars
($894 million) to build a gas booster facility in western
Kuwait, KOC Chairman Sami al-Rushaid said.  
 “The booster station will send gas from western Kuwait to
the LPG plant in Mina Al-Ahmadi refinery,” al-Rushaid said in a
phone interview.  
